---
import { Picture } from "astro:assets";
import localMugPicture from "../assets/lucien-immink.jpg";
---

<div>
  <Picture
    src={localMugPicture}
    formats={["avif", "webp"]}
    alt="Lucien Immink"
    loading="eager"
  />
  <h1>Bio</h1>
  <p>
    A former Java developer that saw the light and embraced Clippy as his
    digital overlord.
  </p>
  <p>
    Over two decades in the front-end field has taught Lucien how we often
    reinvent the wheel to accommodate new shiny frameworks.
  </p>
  <p>
    Now, as a Principal Consultant, his mission is to discover elegant solutions
    for his clients. While we've moved beyond Flash and jQuery, the web platform
    technologies: HTML, CSS, and JavaScript remain essential. Rather than
    battling the platform, let’s embrace it.
  </p>
  <p>
    Lucien is a rewarded Google Developer Expert for Web Technologies and
    capabilities since 2022.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="/talk-list/">🏠 talk-list</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/talk-list/sessions/">📃 sessions</a>
    </li>
    <li><a href="//www.teamrockstars.nl">🏢 The place I work for</a></li>
    <li>
      <a href="//www.jsmusicdb.com">🎼 My spare-time music streamer project</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="//www.github.com/lucienimmink"
        >🧑‍💻 Source-code for all my projects</a
      >
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>

<style>
  div {
    position: sticky;
    top: 10px;
  }
  img {
    border-radius: 50%;
    max-width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 1/1;
    height: auto;
  }
  ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-inline-start: 10px;
    a {
      color: var(--link-color);
      &:hover {
        color: var(--link-hover);
      }
      &:active,
      &:focus {
        color: var(--link-active);
      }
      &:visited {
        color: var(--link-visited);
      }
    }
  }
  @media screen and (max-width: 800px) {
    img {
      max-width: 30%;
      float: right;
      margin-block-start: 30px;
    }
  }
</style>
